<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,266,741,767]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<typeStatus box="[196,258,741,767]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Reitter’s collection at 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" box="[589,685,741,767]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">HNHM</collectionCode>
, is a male fitting the description with 
<typeStatus box="[1160,1213,741,767]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality as Akbes (pinned through the right elytron, right hind claw segment and left middle tarsus missing, remounted and aedeagus dissected) bearing the handwritten labels: “Akbes”, “[yellow square]”, “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1234,816,842]" name="Syria" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Syria</collectingCountry>
, Akbes”, “ 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplirostris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus amplirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[304,369,853,879]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Petri”, “Monotypus, 
<number box="[628,691,853,879]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1904.0">1904</number>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Petri" authorityName="Petri" box="[704,991,853,879]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplirostris">
<emphasis box="[704,922,853,878]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus amplirostris</emphasis>
Petri
</taxonomicName>
, 
<number box="[1004,1026,852,878]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
” red brimmed museum label, and “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Boh., Gultekin" authorityName="Boh., Gultekin" box="[164,550,890,916]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis box="[164,370,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus elegantulus</emphasis>
Boh., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
det. 
<number box="[608,673,890,916]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2008.0">2008</number>
”. It is the 
<typeStatus box="[790,892,890,916]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[931,1152,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName box="[931,1148,890,915]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplirostris">Lixus amplirostris</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
